          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Full of scruples; inclined to scruple; nicely doubtful; hesitating to determine or to act, from a fear of offending or of doing wrong."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Abusing their liberty, to the offense of their weak brethren which were scrupulous."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "2.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Careful; cautious; exact; nice; as, scrupulous abstinence from labor; scrupulous performance of duties."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "3.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Given to making objections; captious."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Equality of two domestic powers Breed scrupulous faction."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
